Class Unit

  • java.lang.Object
    • joueur.BaseGameObject
      • games.newtonian.GameObject

  • public class Unit
extends GameObject
    A unit in the game. May be a manager, intern, or physicist.

    • Method Detail

      • act

        public boolean act(Tile tile)
        Makes the unit do something to a machine or unit adjacent to its tile. Interns sabotage, physicists work. Interns stun physicist, physicist stuns manager, manager stuns intern.
        Parameters:
        tile - The tile the unit acts on.
        Returns:
        True if successfully acted, false otherwise.

      • attack

        public boolean attack(Tile tile)
        Attacks a unit on an adjacent tile.
        Parameters:
        tile - The Tile to attack.
        Returns:
        True if successfully attacked, false otherwise.

      • drop

        public boolean drop(Tile tile,
                    int amount,
                    java.lang.String material)
        Drops materials at the units feet or adjacent tile.
        Parameters:
        tile - The tile the materials will be dropped on.
        amount - The number of materials to dropped. Amounts <= 0 will drop all the materials.
        material - The material the unit will drop. 'redium', 'blueium', 'redium ore', or 'blueium ore'.
        Returns:
        True if successfully deposited, false otherwise.

      • move

        public boolean move(Tile tile)
        Moves this Unit from its current Tile to an adjacent Tile.
        Parameters:
        tile - The Tile this Unit should move to.
        Returns:
        True if it moved, false otherwise.

      • pickup

        public boolean pickup(Tile tile,
                      int amount,
                      java.lang.String material)
        Picks up material at the units feet or adjacent tile.
        Parameters:
        tile - The tile the materials will be picked up from.
        amount - The amount of materials to pick up. Amounts <= 0 will pick up all the materials that the unit can.
        material - The material the unit will pick up. 'redium', 'blueium', 'redium ore', or 'blueium ore'.
        Returns:
        True if successfully deposited, false otherwise.
